HEADWORD: Palinode
<hw>Pal"i*node</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>palinodia</ets>, from Gr. <?/; <grk>pa`lin</grk> again + <?/ a
song. See <er>Ode</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An ode recanting, or
retracting, a former one; also, a repetition of an ode.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A retraction; esp., a formal retraction.</def>
<rj><au>Sandys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palinodial</ent>⟦br⟧
